HEADWORD: Lignoceric
<hw>Lig`no*cer"ic</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧g`n⟦osl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧r"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lignum</ets> wood + <ets>cera</ets>
wax.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an
acid of the formic acid series, found in the tar, wax, or paraffine
obtained by distilling certain kinds of wood, as the beech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

